Pages = {91-97},
Month = {JAN},
Abstract = {Organic semiconductors, which can be widely used in displays, solar
   cells, organic field effect transistors, organic light emitting diodes,
   etc., are a next-generation semiconductor material; the material is
   light and flexible and has the characteristics of being easy and
   inexpensive to make under low-temperature processing conditions. In
   order to improve the performance of organic electronic devices, organic
   semiconductor layer deformation is required, and specifically, these
   charge characteristics should be analyzed. In this study, the
   evaporation rate of the solvent was controlled by changing the substrate
   temperature during the production of the TIPS-pentacene organic
   semiconductor layer. The effect of the crystal alignment effect
   according to the crystal growth conditions on the injection, transfer,
   and accumulation of electric charge was analyzed.},
