   {[}1,2,5]oxadiazolo-{[}3,4-b]quinoxaline backbone has been developed,
   which is based on the sequence of nucleophilic aromatic substitution of
   hydrogen and the Scholl cross-coupling. According to the data from
   electrochemical and photophysical measurements, the synthesized
   compounds can be potentially considered as the narrow-gap (from 1.97 to
   2.34 eV) n-type organic semiconductors, the energy levels of which are
   comparable to those of top commercially available electronic
   semiconductors.},
