   Systems-ICEMS-Annual, Fukuoka, JAPAN, DEC 26-29, 2024},
Abstract = {The use of inverters based on wide bandgap semiconductors has achieved
   even high speeds in inverters. As a result, the ratio of switching
   losses in the inverter increases. Therefore, we drive an inverter based
   on GaN, one of the wide bandgap semiconductors, using a two-phase PWM
