Abstract = {Historically, knowledge of the molecular packing within the crystal
   structures of organic semiconductors has been instrumental in
   understanding their solid-state electronic properties. Nowadays, crystal
   structures are thus becoming increasingly important for enabling
   engineering properties, understanding polymorphism in bulk and in thin
   films, exploring dynamics and elucidating phase-transition mechanisms.
   This review article introduces the most salient and recent results of
   the field.},
